description: If President Joe Biden keeps his promise to sign a ban on TikTok over its ties to the Chinese government, the 81-year-old may rob his reelection campaign of a platform that he and fellow Democrats rely on to reach younger voters.
title: US ban on TikTok would rob Biden, Democrats of 2024 election tool

description: Argentina's Senate on Thursday began a crunch debate on President Javier Milei's sprawling "mega decree" of economic reforms, a major test of the libertarian leader's ability to win over support in a fragmented Congress.
title: Argentina economic "mega decree" faces Senate debate in test for Milei

description: An assault on Leonid Volkov, a top aide to the late Alexei Navalny, in Vilnius on Tuesday was professional and well planned, the head of Lithuania's governmental crisis management centre said on Thursday according to local media.
title: Attack on exiled Navalny aide was well planned, says Lithuania

description: An attack by a hammer-wielding assailant on an exiled top aide to the late Russian opposition leader Alexei Navalny in Vilnius was the work of Russian special services, Lithuanian counter-intelligence said on Thursday.
title: Attack on Navalny aide was work of Russian special services, says Lithuania counter-intelligence

description: U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken will visit South Korea next week and hold a meeting on Monday with his counterpart, Cho Tae-yul, the foreign ministry in Seoul said on Thursday.
title: Blinken to visit South Korea next week, attend Summit for Democracy

description: Britain and Turkey will formally launch negotiations on a new Free Trade Agreement (FTA) on Thursday with a view to including services as well as goods in a new deal.
title: Britain and Turkey launch talks on a new free trade deal

description: Britain said on Thursday it had agreed a security package to protect the borders of the Turks and Caicos Islands - a British Overseas Territory - in response to the risk violence in Haiti could spread.
title: Britain tightens Turks and Caicos security after Haiti violence

description: Britain's Prince William said on Thursday his late mother Princess Diana would have been honoured to see a charity set up in her name doing "inspirational work" to support young people around the world.
title: Britain's Prince William pays tribute to his late mother Princess Diana at awards event

description: China appointed Chen Xiaodong as vice foreign minister, the human resources ministry said in a statement on Thursday.
title: China appoints Chen Xiaodong vice foreign minister, says human resources ministry

description: China's foreign minister, Wang Yi, will visit Australia and New Zealand from March 17 to 21, a spokeseperson said on Thursday at a regular press briefing.
title: China's top diplomat to visit Australia, New Zealand, says foreign minsitry

description: Croatia's lawmakers voted to dissolve parliament on Thursday to pave the way for a parliamentary election that must be held within two months.
title: Croatia dissolves parliament ahead of election by May 12

description: Croatia's historic city of Dubrovnik aims to lure back locals priced out by high tourist prices with a plan next month that includes banning new private rental permits, following the example of other popular destinations across Europe.
title: Croatia's tourist pearl Dubrovnik seeks to reclaim city for locals

description: The four Dutch political parties most likely to form a government will resume negotiations on a looser coalition after far-right leader Geert Wilders', who won the election four months ago, acknowledged he lacked the support to take the top job.
title: Dutch parties resume coalition talks after Wilders forgoes PM role

description: El Salvador's Congress approved on Tuesday a reform to remove income taxes previously imposed on money from abroad, in a move to attract more foreign investment.
title: El Salvador removes income taxes for money from abroad

description: The European Union reached provisional agreement on Thursday on new rules to make legitimate trade in firearms more transparent in a bid to combat illegal trafficking and keep arms out of the hands of criminals.
title: EU agrees new firearm trade rules to curb trafficking

description: Air drops and a maritime corridor will not be enough to make up for supplies transported by trucks into Gaza, where people are on the verge of famine, the European Union's top humanitarian aid official said on Thursday.
title: EU humanitarian chief urges Israel to boost land access to Gaza

description: The EU's foreign policy chief Josep Borrell said on Thursday after holding meetings in Washington that securing new support for Ukraine could not wait since the outcome of the war in Ukraine will be decided this spring and summer.
title: EU's Borrell, in Washington, says outcome of Ukraine war will be decided this spring and summer

description: European Union foreign policy chief Josep Borrell said on Thursday after meetings in Washington that the United States should put more pressure on Israel to allow more aid into Gaza, amid what he called a man-made disaster in the strip.
title: EU's Borrell says US must put more pressure on Israel over Gaza aid

description: Britain unveiled a new definition of extremism on Thursday to counter a surge in hate crimes, raising some concerns it would inhibit free speech and unfairly target Muslim groups.
title: Explainer: What is Britain's new extremism definition?

description: Finnish Prime Minister Petteri Orpo said on Wednesday Russia was gearing up for a "long conflict with the West" and he asked for more spending and coordination on European defence.
title: Finnish leader says Russia is preparing for 'long conflict with the West'

description: French President Emmanuel Macron called President Vladimir Putin's Russia an adversary that would not stop in Ukraine if it defeated Kyiv's troops in the two-year-old conflict, urging Europeans to not be "weak" and to get ready to respond.
title: France's Macron says Europe must be ready if Russia escalates

description: France's lower house of parliament on Thursday approved a bill seeking penalties on ultra-fast fashion products, sold by companies like China's Shein, aimed at helping to offset their environmental impact.
title: French lawmakers approve bill to apply penalties on fast fashion

description: French Sports Minister Amelie Oudea-Castera, who is spearheading the organisation of the Paris summer Olympics, has been placed under investigation for defamation, a public prosecutor said on Thursday.
title: French sports minister put under investigation for defamation

description: Industry ministers from the Group of Seven major democracies agreed on Thursday to align rules on the development of artificial intelligence and to secure supply chains in key sectors such as semiconductors, the Italian presidency said.
title: G7 industry ministers agree to cooperate on AI, supply chains, presidency says

description: The German coalition government needs tighter guidelines for tackling conflicts of interest, though it has been transparent about the influence of lobbying on legislation over the past few years, activist group LobbyControl said on Thursday.
title: German government needs tighter conflict-of-interest guidelines, activists say

description: Germany is midway through a four-year real estate crisis that will lead to more losses and distressed sales of unwanted properties, the head of Commerzbank's real estate business told Reuters.
title: Germany is only halfway through property crisis, says Commerzbank real estate boss

description: An uneasy quiet hung over Haiti's capital Port-au-Prince on Wednesday after the resignation of Prime Minister Ariel Henry, a 74-year-old neurosurgeon who came to power after the assassination of the country's last president.
title: Haiti PM Henry's road to resignation

description: A fire broke out at Haiti's national penitentiary on Thursday morning, according to reports from local media including Radio Television Caraibes (RTVC), with video online showing a thick plume of black smoke billowing out from the facility.
title: Haitian capital's national penitentiary on fire -RTVC

description: A powerful gang leader in Haiti has issued a threatening message aimed at political leaders who would take part in a still unformed transition council for the country, which has been rocked by escalating violence in recent weeks.
title: Haiti's top gang leader threatens politicians, capital jail on fire

description: Philippine President Ferdinand Marcos Jr. told German Chancellor Olaf Scholz the Hague-based International Criminal Court (ICC) has no authority to probe his predecessor's deadly war against drugs.
title: ICC has no authority to probe Philippines, Marcos tells Germany's Scholz

description: Israeli fire killed six Palestinians and wounded dozens of others as crowds of residents awaited aid trucks in Gaza City, Gaza health ministry officials said on Thursday.
title: Israeli fire kills six Gazans awaiting aid trucks, say Palestinian health officials

description: Italy has continued to export arms to Israel, the Italian defence minister said on Thursday, despite assurances last year that the government was blocking such sales following Israel's invasion of the Gaza Strip.
title: Italy arms exports to Israel continued despite block, minister says

description: Jamaican dancehall star Vybz Kartel's conviction for the murder of an associate more than a decade ago was quashed on Thursday, with a London court ruling that attempts to bribe the trial jury meant the conviction was unsafe.
title: Jamaican dancehall star Vybz Kartel wins appeal over murder conviction

description: A Japanese high court ruled that it was "unconstitutional" not to allow same-sex marriage in the country, in a first appeal court ruling on the matter, Japanese media reported on Thursday.
title: Japan high court says not allowing same-sex marriage is unconstitutional, media reports

description: The Kremlin said on Thursday that comments on nuclear weapons that Russian President Vladimir Putin made in an interview with state media did not constitute a threat to use them, and accused the U.S. of deliberately taking the remarks out of context.
title: Kremlin says Putin didn't threaten to use nuclear weapons, U.S. took him out of context

description: The parliament of Kyrgyzstan on Thursday adopted a bill styled on Russia's "foreign agents" law that international observers fear will restrict the work of nongovernmental organisations and independent media in the Central Asian country.
title: Kyrgyzstan parliament adopts Russian-style "foreign agents" bill

description: French President Emmanuel Macron awarded billionaire Bernard Arnault, the CEO of LVMH, the country's highest honour at a Paris ceremony on Wednesday attended by superstar Beyonce and Tesla co-founder Elon Musk, French media reported.
title: Macron awards highest French honour to LVMH CEO at star-studded event -reports

description: An earthquake with a preliminary magnitude of 5.8 hit eastern Japan early on Friday, the Japan Meteorological Agency said.
title: Magnitude 5.8 earthquake hits Japan's Fukushima

description: The association overseeing Chinese journalists issued a rare statement of protest after reporters were blocked by local residents and security guards while trying to report on the aftermath of a blast outside Beijing.
title: Media harassment after China restaurant blast sparks protest, public criticism

description: The European Union's top humanitarian aid official said on Thursday he had seen no evidence from Israel to back its accusations against staff from the U.N. Palestinian refugee agency (UNRWA), which should continue playing a "critical" role in Gaza.
title: No evidence from Israel to back UNRWA accusations, says EU humanitarian chief

description: A group of Nordic donors has raised nearly one million euros to treat Ukrainian children traumatised by war, initially in an online clinic which they hope to turn into a new children's hospital to be built in Ukraine if more donors join in.
title: Nordic donors plan online clinic to treat Ukrainian children's war traumas

description: Norway's King Harald has been discharged from the hospital after receiving a permanent pacemaker earlier this week and is doing well, the royal court said on Thursday.
title: Norway's King Harald has been discharged from hospital after getting pacemaker

description: Behind the doors of a small, non-descript office in the heart of New Delhi lies the headquarters of an electoral trust run by just two men that is the largest-known donor to India’s ruling Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP), according to a Reuters review of public records.
title: Obscure trust links India's top businesses with Modi's election war chest

description: Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas named Mohammad Mustafa as prime minister of the Palestinian Authority (PA), the state-run Palestinian news agency WAFA said on Thursday.
title: Palestinian President Abbas appoints new prime minister of Palestinian Authority

description: The Philippine's former first lady Imelda Marcos is set to leave hospital on Thursday, after suffering from fever and a slight pneumonia, her son President Ferdinand Marcos Jr. said.
title: Philippines' former first lady Imelda Marcos set to leave hospital

description: Polish opposition party Law and Justice (PiS) has asked the top court to declare laws allowing a parliamentary committee to summon the central bank chief for hearings unconstitutional in a bid to block a probe planned by the ruling coalition.
title: Polish opposition asks top court to block central bank head probe

description: Pope Francis has no intention of resigning as he feels that his health is good enough to allow him to carry on, he says in a new book whose excerpts were published by Italy's Corriere della Sera newspaper on Thursday.
title: Pope says option of resigning is only 'a distant hypothesis'

description: Local government officials in China's Sanhe county, near Beijing, said on Thursday they had started an investigation into the cause of a massive explosion at a shop selling fried chicken that left 7 dead and 27 injured.
title: Probe begins after 7 killed, 27 injured in fried chicken shop explosion in China

description: President Vladimir Putin appealed on Thursday to voters, including in annexed parts of Ukraine, to be united in determining Russia's future by casting ballots in this week's presidential election which he is all but certain to win.
title: Putin asks voters, including in annexed Ukrainian areas, to determine Russia's future

description: Spain's lower house of parliament on Thursday approved an amnesty bill for Catalan separatists, clearing a major hurdle for a law set to define Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez's second term - and one that has led to protests and annoyed judges.
title: Relief for Spain's socialists as Catalan amnesty bill clears parliamentary hurdle

description: reuters.com
title: reuters.com

description: reuters.com
title: reuters.com

description: Russia is believed to have jammed the satellite signal on an aircraft used by defence minister Grant Shapps to travel from Poland back to Britain, a government source and journalists travelling with him said on Thursday.
title: Russia believed to have jammed signal on UK defence minister's plane - source

description: Russian forces launched three-dozen drones across several Ukrainian regions overnight, hitting civilian infrastructure, authorities in Ukraine said on Thursday.
title: Russia targets Ukraine with latest mass drone strike

description: A former Russian soldier who had fought in Ukraine was sentenced to 20 years in prison on Thursday for starting a fire in a nightclub that killed 13 people, Russian media reported.
title: Russian ex-soldier gets 20-yr sentence for starting deadly nightclub fire

description: German Chancellor Olaf Scholz assured Ukraine its international partners will cooperate closely on military support in a telephone call with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy, a government spokesperson said on Thursday.
title: Scholz, Zelenskiy discuss military support, peace in phone call

description: U.S. Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer said on Thursday that Israel must make "significant course corrections" to achieve lasting peace with the Palestinians.
title: Schumer says Israel needs 'significant course corrections' for peace

description: A second ship with food aid to Gaza was being loaded in Cyprus, a charity arranging the mission said on Thursday, as the first ship in a pilot trial of maritime deliveries neared the besieged Palestinian enclave.
title: Second ship loaded with Gaza aid from Cyprus, says charity

description: Slovakia's new government led by populist Robert Fico launched a planned revamp of public broadcaster RTVS on Thursday in a bid to bring it under direct state control, raising alarm at the television and radio station as well as with EU media.
title: Slovakia raises alarm with planned revamp of public broadcaster

description: Taiwan and China authorities dispatched teams to join a rescue mission for a boat that capsized near Taiwan-controlled Kinmen islands on Thursday morning, according to Taiwan's United Daily News and a senior Taiwan official briefed on the matter.
title: Taiwan, China dispatch teams to join boat rescue mission near Taiwan-controlled islands

description: Thailand's former Prime Minister Thaksin Shinawatra arrived by private jet on Thursday to visit his northern hometown of Chiang Mai for the first time since fleeing the country after a military coup in 2006.
title: Thai ex-PM Thaksin visits hometown for first time since 2006 ouster

description: Thousands in Israel took to the streets on Thursday in two separate protests, one demanding an immediate release of hostages from Gaza and another calling for drafting ultra-Orthodox Jewish men into the military.
title: Thousands in Israel protest for hostages release, conscription of ultra-Orthodox

description: Senior Turkish officials will discuss security issues, particularly Turkey's operations against the outlawed Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) in Iraq, with their counterparts in Baghdad on Thursday, a Turkish defence ministry official said.
title: Turkey to discuss 'common understanding' on security with Iraq -official

description: British Prime Minister Rishi Sunak said on Thursday that he would not hold a general election in early May, in the strongest indication yet that the national vote would take place later this year.
title: UK PM Rishi Sunak rules out holding an election in early May

description: Britain unveiled a new definition of extremism on Thursday in response to an eruption of hate crimes against Jews and Muslims since the Oct. 7 Hamas attacks on Israel, although critics said the change risked infringing on freedom of speech.
title: UK unveils new extremism definition amid rise in hate crimes against Jews, Muslims

description: Russia's staging of elections in occupied territories of Ukraine is illegal and void, the Ukrainian Foreign Ministry said on Thursday, urging international partners not to recognise the results.
title: Ukraine calls Russia's election in occupied territories null and void

description: When Oleg Bazylewicz, an artist and writer, signed up for military duty on the day that Russia invaded his native Ukraine, he readied the two things he valued most - his watercolours and his block flute, a musical instrument.
title: Ukrainian soldier uses mud and ash to paint scenes of nature and war

description: For families who fled Israeli bombardment of southern Lebanon, being away from home is especially hard in the Islamic fasting month of Ramadan - a time when they usually enjoy special meals together but this year are scattered by conflict.
title: Uprooted by war, Lebanese yearn for home at Ramadan

description: The Biden Administration is expected to impose new sanctions on two illegal outposts in the occupied West Bank that were used as a base for attacks by "extremist" Israeli settlers against Palestinians, Axios reported late on Wednesday, citing three U.S. officials.
title: US expected to impose new sanctions against occupied West Bank outposts, Axios reports

description: The U.S. on Thursday finalized its draft U.N. Security Council resolution on the Israel-Hamas war, traditionally the final step before asking for a vote on the text that would back international efforts to broker an immediate ceasefire as part of a hostage release deal.
title: US locks in UN resolution backing efforts to broker Gaza truce

description: The United States will open an embassy in Vanuatu "imminently" and is working to get the approval of the parliament in Kiribati for a mission, the top U.S. diplomat for East Asia said on Thursday, while reiterating warnings to Pacific Island countries of the dangers of agreements with China.
title: US says to open Vanuatu embassy 'imminently', warns of China deals

description: The U.S. Senate voted overwhelmingly on Thursday to confirm career diplomat Dennis Hankins as ambassador to Haiti, filling the key diplomatic post in the troubled Caribbean country for the first time in nearly 2-1/2 years.
title: US Senate confirms Biden nominee Hankins to be ambassador to Haiti

description: U.S.-South Korean talks on sharing the cost of keeping American troops in South Korea are on track and ahead of schedule, but the U.S. side does not necessarily see a hard deadline ahead of the November U.S. election, a senior Biden administration official told Reuters.
title: US-South Korea defense talks on track, but November not a hard deadline-US official

description: Venezuela opposition leader Maria Corina Machado is facing increasing pressure from her allies to choose a substitute to potentially run in her place in the July presidential election, five sources with knowledge of the matter said.
title: Venezuela opposition candidate pressured by allies to choose a substitute, sources say

description: Vietnam's imports of weapons last year slowed to a trickle as it worked to diversify supplies away from Russia, data released on Monday show, while experts warned the country could be vulnerable during a regional conflict.
title: Vietnam arms imports drop to a trickle despite regional tensions

description: Vietnam's foreign ministry on Thursday said international law and the rights and interests of other countries must be respected, responding to a question about China's demarcation earlier this month of a baseline in the Gulf of Tonkin.
title: Vietnam urges respect of international law as China draws Gulf of Tonkin baseline

description: The U.S. Central Command (CENTCOM) said the Iranian-backed Houthi militants fired one anti-ship ballistic missile from Yemen into the Gulf of Aden, but it caused no damage to any vessels.
title: Yemen's Houthis fired missile in Gulf of Aden, no damage reported, US says

description: The Russian-controlled management of the Zaporizhzhia nuclear power plant, the largest in Europe, said on Thursday that the Ukrainian army had shelled a critical infrastructure facility at the plant.
title: Zaporizhzhia nuclear plant reports shelling by Ukraine army
